definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: Under government policy, British nuclear submarines carry a maximum of 48 warheads.
sentences.chinese: 據政府政策規定，英國核潛艇最多可裝載48顆彈頭。

sentences.english: BELLISARIO: To be honest, what's changed for me is my schedule.
sentences.chinese: 老實說，變化最多的是我的日程表。

sentences.english: Fig1. Paper is staple food supposing office is restaurant.
sentences.chinese: 如果辦公室是個餐館，紙應該是每天消耗最多的主食。

sentences.english: First of all, it will only be a minute or two at a time, maybe once or twice a lecture.
sentences.chinese: 首先，每次只有一兩分鐘，一堂課最多不超過兩次。

sentences.english: Please, Lord, give me no more than 10years.
sentences.chinese: 請上帝最多讓我活10年吧。

sentences.english: They're cheap, a few bucks at the most.
sentences.chinese: 蒸籠很便宜，最多幾美元。

sentences.english: In fact, we import more gasoline into Afghanistan than any other product.
sentences.chinese: 事實上，我們從阿富汗進口最多的物資就是汽油。

sentences.english: Indah has the highest number of flood victims.
sentences.chinese: 運達的水災災民的人數最多。

sentences.english: Where are Chinese gooseberries most massively planted?
sentences.chinese: 種植中國獼猴桃最多的國家是哪一個？

sentences.english: Yili area is one of the most abundant protected area in Xinjiang province.
sentences.chinese: 伊犁地區是新疆自然保護區數量最多的地區。

sentences.english: But apples are also one of the most pesticide-contaminated fruits and vegetables.
sentences.chinese: 但是蘋果也是農藥殘留最多的蔬果之一。

sentences.english: The big change they made to this one was the ending.
sentences.chinese: 在這個故事中，他們改變最多的是結局。

sentences.english: Lin Tao won the most votes.
China is the country that sends the most students abroad for studies and researches.
sentences.chinese: 中國是世界上出國前留學生最多的國家。

sentences.english: I promise never to eat more than one serving of okra again.
sentences.chinese: 我保證我以後最多就只吃一份秋葵。

sentences.english: They had several dates that went no further than a good-night kiss.
sentences.chinese: 他們有許多約會，最多不超過一晚安接吻。

definition: number of times/frequency/order number (in a series)/power (math.)/degree of a polynomial (math.)
classifier for birds and certain animals, one of a pair, some utensils, vessels etc
up to/no less than/as much as
can be counted on one's fingers (idiom)/very few
